    "With the obvious slow movement achieved with their long legs (Cartmill, 1983; Heinrich, 2002; Carsten, 2010), it is natural to propose that longer legs were gradually developed in order to be taller, since a higher body profile makes humans less vulnerable to predator attacks (e.g., Blake, 2023).",
    "Long hair on top of a head: Nina Jablonski suggested that it was evolutionarily advantageous for hominins to retain the hair on their heads in order to protect the scalp as they walked upright under the intense African sun (Jablonski, 2008).",
